    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>A Climate Pact Without America</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Rob Setili letter holds United States should take lead in lowering carbon dioxide emissions (July 24 article)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''178 Nations Reach a Climate Accord; U.S. Only Looks On'' (front page, July 24): The United States leads global innovation. If any country could lower carbon dioxide emissions and compete globally under tougher environmental laws, it is America. The United States led the world in shifting employment to a service and information economy. We depend less on manufacturing and can stomach new restrictions on burning fossil fuels. We should be leading this change.</p>
        <p>ROB SETILI  Atlanta, July 24, 2001</p>
      </block>
